<code>nobreak-fade.el</code> offers a few "nobreak" functions for <code>fill-nobreak-predicate</code> (see FillParagraph).  Get it from

: http://user42.tuxfamily.org/nobreak-fade/index.html

The nobreaks include

* Danging single-letter "I" or "A" at the start or end of a sentence
* Emacs M-x foo
* Emacs docstring URL `' and an Info node `' workaround
* TeX maths <code>$x ... y$</code>

If you use Emacs 21 the <code>nobreak-fade-add</code> function can help manage <code>fill-nobreak-predicate</code> as a single function (it's a hook in Emacs 22 and up).

